description.plain:
“24k” flows in smooth hip house energy and features Zimbabwe-Australian Tkay Maidza’s classic rap-sung combos. It’s featured as the second track, and later a single on 2020’s critically acclaimed Last Year Was Weird, Vol. 2.

Produced by frequent collaborator and friend Dan Farber the song features an intro and outro by an unknown radio broadcaster. The broadcaster runs Last Year Was Weird (LYWW) Radio, which is where the EP title comes from. Links to LYWW radio are made in numerous songs on the EP, especially “PB Jam.”

description.plain: “Where Is My Mind?” is a cover of The Pixies' 1988 song of the same name. That song was never released as a single, but remains The Pixies' most popular song, aided by it’s prominent use in the 1999 film Fight Club. Tkay’s version is a synthetic, hip-hop take on the original, featuring breakbeat drums, a synth lead playing the original guitar part, and a Moog bass. The repeated “Where is my, where is my, where is my…” in the intro and post-choruses are also unique to this version.
